Wish list:
  - when we drop an entry candidate picture due to some reason
    (TS delay too big, field conflict, etc), we should also drop the following
    non-entry pictures AS SOON AS POSSIBLE to reduce buffer fullness.
  - in the splice request, we should add a parameter to indicate whether we
    should pick an entry candidate to maximize or minimize the tsDelay of the
    new channel.  Maximize means to avoid picture dropping (AD), minimize
    means to minimize buffer level.



2/1/00

  Outstanding DPI issues:
    - BUG: rate conversion does not work for Philip source
      Reason: mis-association of PES header to picture
              (same reason as for the Harmonic Lightway DTS jump problem)
      Status: fixed.

    - BUG: HITS splicing always timeout after PES header association fix.
      The other channel's DTS can not be found!
      Fixed by moving the code with fix B-picture DTS problem ahead of
      the DTS check.
      Status: fixed.

    - PCR drift warning from Mux at splice point.
      Decided not to do anything to handle the PCR discontinuity.
      Status: dropped.

    - BUG: Ad insertion with SeaChange accumulate channels at FORCED SWITCH.
      Reason: Timeout signal is sent too early (at splicer instead of at
              output task after sending the last picture).  As a result, the
              delete channel PPC message was ignored because channel is
              not OFF yet.
      Solution: Delay the sending of Splice Indication message to the Output
              task if the last picture sent to mux has not yet been output.
              Otherwise send the indication from the Splicer.  That means,
              for successful splice and late forced splice, splice indication
              will be sent from the Output Task.  For timeout-stay case and
              early forced splice, splice indication will be sent in the
              Splice Task.
              One problem in the forced splice case is to determine whether
              the last picture sent to mux has been output by the output task.
              To do this, we add a new variable lastPicStat in ChanInfo to
              point to the last PicStat sent to mux.  It is initialized to
              NULL at channel start up.  If this picture is sent out by the
              Output Task, lastPicStat will be set to NULL.  This way, we
              can tell whether the last picture sent to mux has been output
              by comparing lastPicStat to NULL.

    - BUG: entry field modification is wrong for closed GOP

    - ENHANCEMENT: alignment with mux by stealing B pictures

    - ISSUE: found out from Brian that when playing back to back ads, there is
      a small (about 100 ms) gap between the ads!  Currently our splicer
      is not able to handle that.


2/2/00
    - ENAHNCEMENT: currently the first entry candidate is kept in the BG queue
        until queue overflow, in which case the next candidate will be
        searched.  This however gives large tsDelay in general.  A better
        algo will be to look for latest entry candidate, and drop all the
        preceeding pictures in the queue.
      Note that this change may not work for channel or Ad with confined
      time span!


