2/4/00
    Seems the FPGA code has problem (dropping or repeating TPs) when the signal
    goes up and down, like the SeaChange feed.

    The old FPGA has similar problem, but only at around end of sequence and
    the problem occurs much less frequent.

    Switched back to use old FPGA code and clean cut module.

    BUG: After false switch from AD1 to AD2, it switches back to Live very
         quickly.
    Reason: at false switch, refPicNo is not set.

    BUG: forced switch from AD1 to AD2
    Reason: AD2 1st picture PTS is larger than AD1 last picture PET!
    Seems we need to further delay the requested splice time of the first AD.
    More critical problem: the SeaChange API assumes we do splicing BEFORE
    the requested time!


