2/8/00
    Delay the request splice time by 1 sec, and try to adjust parameters
    to avoid Ad picture dropping.

    BUG: when long delay is added to the request splice time, the leading
         B pictures get dropped.
    Reason: pCh->closedGop get replaced by the next GOP in the Ad, which
         turns out to be an open GOP!
    Solution: move closedGop flag from ChanInfo to PicStat.  In doSplice(),
         closedGopFlag of the entry picture (I picture) is used to set
         the startingFlag.


2/9/00
  JC found out that the new FPGA start code search functionality cannot work
  with old DVB IO board (v2).  We need new DVB IO board (v4) to run the new
  FPGA code and use the FPGA start code search functionality.
  JC also found that we need to use the latest mux (ver 108) to have DPI
  to work.  Old mux code (ver 106) will fail.

  ** We later found out that we need to set a environment variable hidden in
  the DVBIO board to turn on loading FPGA from PPC.  After this is done,
  both old and new board work fine!

  Forced switch after about an hour (15 breaks).  Forced switch due to TP
  dropping at the input.  Problem: too many pictures waiting on the buffer.
  Need to reduce max queue size.

  BUG: In JC's test, we will have problem of bad pidbuf pointer inside
       extractTpPayload().  Since we are outputing at 27MHz it seems to have
       some problem with statmux rate allocation.  This happens in about 10 min.

  Status: I have able to splice 2 back-to-back ads into Harmonic source.
          Both inputs are at 8 Mbps and output is set to 6 Mbps.


2/10/00
  Overnight run died with bad PidBuf pointer in extractTpPayload()
  in about 30 minutes!   The bad pointer points inside pidChansHandle.
  It seems like this always happen on picture with SEQ END code.

  BUG: seems like when we insert a sequence end code at the beginning of
       the new channel, we forget to update the firstTp pointer of the
       entry picture.

  After the if condition for sequence end code insertion is removed, the
  code runs much longer.  Without rate conversion, its runs for about 1.5 hr
  before having CC problem.  Then it has about 18 CCs in 10 minutes.  Finally
  the PPC died.  No false switch so far.

  However, with rate conversion on, extractTpPayload() bad pointer shows up
  again, in about a few minutes.


2/11/00
  BUG: A bug was found in extractTpPayload() which has been causing these bad
       PidBuf pointer problems.  We should not look for the next TP in case we
       have reach the last TP in picture.  Otherwise, if the current turns out
       to be the last picture in the queue, then the next TP pointer will not
       pass checkPidBufLink().
  SOLUTION: Use in extractTpPayload() a version of getPidBuf() and pidBufFree()
       which do not check PidBuf link.  This will create a security hole but
       should fix the above bug.


