2/24/00
  Picture counting:
    In PicStat:
      picCnt: count output pictures, continuous across splice point 
      inPicCnt: count input pictures of a channel, maybe reset at chan init
      picNo: display picture number??
      refPicNo: picNo of latest referernce picture

    In ChanInfo:
      inPicCnt: input picture counter
      outPicCnt: output picture counter
      picNoBase: picNo of 1st displayed picture in channel
      gopPicNoBase: picNo of 1st displayed picture in current GOP
      prevRefPicNo: picNo of last anchor frame

    There are two ways to counter pictures:
      - in coding order (inPicCnt, outPicCnt)
      - in display order (picNo)

    Coding order is used for labeling.
    For picture based splicing, it is the display order that we use to
    determine splice point.
 
  ** New way of implementing background channel processing in forced switch:
    Search for the first picture with sequence start code
    whose PTS >= current time + 0x6000
    (default init value between PCR and DTS used by statmux).
    Drop all pictures before this picture.
    If such a picture is not found in the queue, then re-init the channel.

  ** Added a new mode of splicing: EOS_BASED.  Will switch when EOS header is
     found in the old channel.
    Use spliceTime in FG channel to track the PET of the latest anchor picture.


2/25/00
    isLeadingBPic() fixed the bug.
    - New API effort:
        new chan's tsDelay: easy
        new chan's first output TP arrival time: may not be the real signal
            arrival time if we drop picture at start.
        old chan's last output TP arrival time: to handle forced switch also,
            we copy arrival time of the TP with EOS.
        gap in splice point: new EOS splice mode allow old chan PET to be
            different than new chan PTS.  In this case, splice time is
            defined to be the old chan PET.

      Note: need to verify with Wayne whether new TPs generated by cleanCut
            have correct TS info.

    EOS based splicing:
      When FG EOS detected, one of the following cases is true:
        1. BG channel has not even started (no TP received yet)
        2. BG channel has started, but SEQ HDR not found yet
        3. BG SEQ HDR found, but PTS > PET (dead time exists)
        4. BG SEQ HDR found, and PTS <= PET (no dead time)

      If splice indication is to be sent after the last picture of the FG
      channel is sent, then deadTime can only be determined in 3 and 4.

