2/28/00
  Debug EOS mode
  - The EOS mode seems pretty reliable!  Although it has visual breakup
    at splice, its looks much better than forced switch.
    (Note that EOS mode IS a variation of forced switch!)

  Why do we need to want for both channel to be ready before we do the switch?
  Should we just do the switch as soon as the old channel is ready?

  - New channel may have problem.  The alternative method will always do the
    switch (like TIMEOUT_FORCE_SWITCH).
  - There may be gap between exit point and entry point.
    For live new channel, we can assume that we always buffer up enough
    pictures so that as soon as the old channel is ready, a entry candidate
    with no dead time can always be found.
    For signal with time boundary, there will be a gap anyway IF WE CANNOT
    postpone the switch.  (We can choose a later exit candidate though).
  - Field parity conflict: will need picture info from new channel to determine.

  To do:
    - integrate with new audio (Wayne)
    - support new API


